wikipedia_page.main: Henry Telford Hayman (20 November 1853 – 8 February 1941) was an English freemason, clergyman and amateur cricketer.

response: Another brother, Bradbury Norton, and a nephew, Henry Hayman, also played first-class cricket.
*Henry Hayman (educationist) (1823–1904), British educator, headmaster of Rugby School
*Henry Hayman Toulmin (1807–1871), wealthy British ship owner, became Justice of the Peace and High Sheriff of Hertfordshire
